    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, \"dangerously weak\"? that's a pretty strong way to put it. aren't there actual ethical frameworks that say human rights should come before national laws? like, isn't ignoring a person in need inherently wrong regardless of what country they're in? why is sovereignty more \"undeniable\" than basic human empathy?",
