      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the social contract thing, but it feels like you're basically saying that people's lives are just secondary to administrative stability. isn't it a bit reductive to say humanitarian arguments \"crumble\" just because they're difficult to manage? it feels like you're dismissing the actual suffering of individuals as a secondary concern to \"order.\"",
